UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407686900308
AB  - The importance that functional structure plays in the analysis of producer behavior is well known and responsible for the empirical tests of input separability hypotheses found in the contemporary literature. Unfortunately, to our knowledge all such tests have been conducted under the maintained assumption of full factor input equilibrium. In this paper we propose and implement a method for testing functional structure hypotheses when the behavioral units are permitted to be in disequilibrium. The results of this more general test provide less support for the existence of input separability in two-digit manufacturing than previously reported by the authors using tests assuming full equilibrium.
